11.3 Requests 
Recognizing that requests for assistance are impositions on another person’s time, 
speakers can couch their requests in the form of a question that at least gives the potential 
benefactor a choice; or they can begin the request with a covering phrase like máfan nǐ 
‘may I bother you’ or tuō nǐ yí jiàn shì ‘mind if I ask a favor (entrust you one M thing)’ – 
the latter more common when the request involves an item of business rather than just 
passing help.  
 

